We have been providing vacation rental apartments for over 10 years across the East Coast. We are known for our distinctively furnished apartments in popular locations, and for our attentive service. You鈥檒l find that our rates are quite reasonable. If you're looking for a safe, comfortable place with fabulous amenities and Wi-Fi (we know you need the Wi-Fi!) in the Boston MA area, Washington DC, Miami FL or very close to NYC in Jersey City or Hoboken, we'd love to host you. Many of the buildings where our apartments are located feature amenities such as beautiful lobbies, 24 hour front desk staff, fitness centers, business centers, recreation rooms, indoor or outdoor pools and whirlpools. If you are traveling with children, some buildings offer playgrounds (many buildings are near public playgrounds as well) or indoor playrooms. Depending on the location, you can stay for just a few days, a week, a month or more. 

We offer an assortment of short-term apartments in sizes ranging from a studio to three bedrooms that are fully furnished with all the comforts of home. Our local staff meticulously prepares your apartment before your arrival, and we offer 24 hour assistance for any emergencies after business hours. When you arrive at your apartment, the beds will be made, towels and bath amenities will be stocked in the bathrooms, and the coffee maker will be set up in the kitchen with some sample coffees, sweetener and creamer (teabags too if that is your preference) to start your morning off properly. If you鈥檇 like to cook a meal, the kitchen is stocked with dishes, cutlery, glassware and pots and pans. The living room is set up with a TV and cable channels, and the Wi-Fi router password and instructions will be prominently displayed so you can get connected quickly. You can also make local and toll-free phone calls at no charge. 

Please contact us to confirm the exact availability of the apartment you are interested in. We鈥檇 love to host you (and your family) for your vacation or business trip.

Who we are: Our Principles

1) Growing Our Alumni Community:
We don鈥檛 require any extra/hidden fees to maximize our profits. Instead, our focus is on growing our alumni community. We believe that our services and fair pricing speak for themselves among our guests. Our alumni posted 700+ reviews from 2019 to 2021. What鈥檚 more, 80% of the reviews gave us five stars and 97% awarded more than four stars. Our alumni community spans the globe with 87 unique nationalities, and it has been expanding. We look forward to serving all our new guests: our alumni of tomorrow.
鈥?

There鈥檚 no math required. The price for our one-month minimum stay is simple and fair, no matter how long you stay with us. Our one-month price is already competitive (averaging $1,200 to $2,200, with 80% of our 150 rooms under $1,900 per month), compared to others鈥?discounted prices for three- to six-month stays. In 2020, 50%+ of our customers extended their original stay by a few months. There鈥檚 really no substitute for all-inclusive furnished rentals and a co-living environment, with a furnished private room, that鈥檚 ready for you on day one.
鈥?
鈥?) Increasing Value for the Local Property Industry:
We provide co-living communities for our guests by helping property owners draw more value from under-managed residential properties. We care about our customer community, of course, but we鈥檙e also excited about uniting property owners, vendors, and our team on one digital platform.
鈥?
鈥?) Privacy Is the Priority:
There are no required social events. Our priority is providing privacy, a quiet environment, and security for all our guests. Our team will take care of cleaning the common spaces every week, so that our kitchen/dining areas are always comfortable. But if you want to expand your network or social circle, our office at WeWork offers you day/after-work communities. We just moved our headquarters to the newest WeWork offices in Long Island City, which is easily accessible by all subway lines.


鈥?) 10 Years Perfecting the Co-Living Mindset:
Our founder started this business in his apartment after he couldn鈥檛 find appropriately priced accommodation for his first three months in New York. But our whole team has experienced co-living firsthand, so we understand what the customer feels and will need next. 鈥淲e live and breathe co-living: first as roommates, and now serving our co-living guests.鈥?鈥?
鈥?) A Sustainable Business Model in the Sharing Economy:
We won鈥檛 invest in luxury buildings like hotels or event spaces. We rent existing empty apartments and townhouses from the owners, put IKEA-type furniture in, and list the clean rooms on multiple digital platforms. We grow by our operational profit base, which comes from guests being charged fair prices and the revenue owners receive. However, what drives our growth is not the number of rooms, but our deep understanding of how to care for guests and rooms 24/7, and the intangible value within them.
鈥?
鈥?) Our Vision - Making Dreams Come True:
CrossOver鈥檚 goal is to help our guests achieve their goals and dreams by providing the most affordable and flexible housing environment available. But it doesn鈥檛 stop here. I am an anthropology professor and run a cultural center in downtown Manhattan. We are bilingual in Spanish, English and fluent in French who enjoy good music and good conversation.

**THE MOTT HAVEN HISTORIC NEIGHBORHOOD** 
We are located on a historically landmarked sector of Mott Haven with old townhouses and brownstones, deemed the "prettiest block in the South Bronx" by Ephemeral New York (URL HIDDEN)

The first Bronx subway stop on the 6 train from Manhattan leaves you a block from 138th Street and Alexander Avenue. Once known as 鈥淒octors Row鈥?and 鈥淭he Irish Fifth Avenue,鈥?Alexander Avenue between here and 141st Street boasts gorgeous row houses dating to the 1870s. 

The house is next door to the police precinct and one short block to the first Bronx branch of the New York Public Library .

There are new bars and restaurants a few short blocks from our place: La Morada, Mott Haven Bar and Grill, Ceetay, Charlie's, and others. You can also try the fantastic authentic Dominican and Puerto Rican cuisine nearby.

Take a quiet respite at La Finca del Sur and Brook Park, two lovely community gardens within blocks from the apartment. this last one offers bike and kayac tours of the Bronx River during the summer.

The house is a few subway stops from the following museums: 
Bronx Museum of the Arts 
The Met 
The MoMA 
Studio Museum in Harlem 
The Guggenheim 
The Whitney Museum of American Art 
Gagosian Gallery

The Local Stay, founded in 2008 and offers hundreds of short-term and long-term rental properties in Amsterdam, Barcelona, Buenos Aires, London, New York, New-Jersey, Paris, Rome, Tel Aviv and more. Our apartments inventory includes both corporate apartments and privately owned flats, making The Local Stay the perfect option for business travelers, corporate relocation clients and those on sabbatical, as well as foreign students.
The Local Stay makes the process of renting furnished short- and long-term apartments absolutely transparent, so renters and property owners alike can rest easy.
At The Local Stay, our goal is to take the guess work out of it, carefully curating apartments so that travelers experience the true pulse of the city. And, since each property owner is personally vetted by The Local Stay team, travelers can rest assured that their stays will be safe and secure. Better vetting means that travelers get the most exclusive apartments in the most central locations, while greater involvement by The Local Stay means that property owners can list it and leave it as we handle communication with renters
With options for everyone, The Local Stay provides personalized service so that every traveler can stay like a local.

I'm Randy Settenbrino the artist who created the Historic Blue Moon and have been on Orchard Street from my teenage years as well as most of my professional life. The historic facades, merchants and eclectics give it the ambiance of a back lot 
from MGM. There is a soulfulness loved by the authentic locals as well as the out of Towner鈥檚 that gravitate here. The sensation of high energy is brought about by the contrast of old New York with the vigor of visitors to a burgeoning city. It's just the perfect scene to begin a story of your own or with someone of your choosing. There is room to mix in the crowd or make yourself noticed in a myriad of settings for human interaction; something surely missed in our time of impersonal communication. Any article about Orchard Street is incomplete without the newsworthy story of how the soul of a 5-story tenement filled with artifacts and personal affects became a stately eighth story hotel. Only a visit to the Historic Blue Moon can make one really understand how only on Orchard Street could art and history collide into such an elegant design.
The Historic Blue Moon was chosen as one in hundred and fifty hotels in the Western Hemisphere to check into by National Geographic as well as the recipient of over forty major articles.

鈥?) A Sustainable Business Model in the Sharing Economy:

PLEASE NOTE:  DUE TO COVID-19, AND SARS-CoV-2, THE VIRUS THAT CAUSES COVID-19, I HAVE ESTABLISHED RIGOROUS CLEANING PROCEDURES THAT HAVE BEEN MAINTAINED IN MY APARTMENT SINCE FEBRUARY 2020, AND THESE PROCEDURES WILL BE MAINTAINED BETWEEN AIRBNB STAYS, BEFORE GUESTS ARRIVE, AND DURING STAYS AFTER GUESTS RETURN TO THE APARTMENT, SPECIFICALLY:

1.  CLEANING TOUCHABLE SURFACES WITH CDC-APPROVED "FANTASTIK DISINFECTANT", OR PROPERLY DILUTED BLEACH, ON ALL COMMON TOUCHABLE SURFACES.

2.  SURGICAL GLOVES WILL BE AVAILABLE FOR ALL GUESTS WHO WANT TO USE THEM, EITHER OUTSIDE THE APARTMENT OR INSIDE.  

THESE GLOVES ARE WASHABLE, AND CAN ALSO BE STERILIZED WITH COVID SANITIZERS, WHICH IS ADVISABLE BECAUSE RUBBER GLOVES PICK UP BACTERIA AND VIRUSES, BUT THEY PROVIDE A BARRIER FOR YOUR HANDS IF STERILIZED.

3.  ALL BEDDING WILL BE LAUNDERED IN HOT WATER AND SOAP BETWEEN STAYS.  GUESTS MAY DO THEIR LAUNDRY IN THE BASEMENT.

4.  THE BATHROOM SHOWER/TUB, INCLUDING THE GLASS DOORS, WILL BE CLEANED AND THEN SANITIZED BETWEEN STAYS WITH FANTASTIK DISINFECTANT, THE FLOORS WILL BE CLEANED BETWEEN STAYS, AND THE TOILET WILL BE CLEANED/DISINFECTEDWITH BLEACH.

Other than with the rigorous cleaning I have instituted, lol, I'm very easy going and easy to be around.  

I ALWAYS WEAR A MASK AND SURGICAL GLOVES WHEN I GO OUTSIDE THE APARTMENT, AND I UNDRESS IN MY BEDROOM, STERILIZE MY 2 MASKS AND GLOVES AFTER THAT, WASH AND THEN CHANGE CLOTHES. 

I sterilize any knobs or light switches I touched when I entered. 

I do NOT expect guests to do the same, but I will clean doorknobs and light switches after guests return, and I will maintain an appropriate distance if and when my Airbnb guests want me to socialize with them.

I will not have neighbor or other visitors.

I tend to like guests who are responsible, who can be independent, and who will try to keep the kitchen and bathroom basically clean, although I and my roommate will also be cleaning in those areas. 

Although the guest bathroom is shared with one person between 6 or 7 P.M. and 6:30 A.M., my apartment roommate in the smaller bedroom is very clean.  I use the 2nd bathroom, which is in my bedroom (ensuite).

I am friendly and don't mind hanging out with guests sometimes, but I keep to myself when I'm home.   

Occasional smoking will be ok in the guest room, with the door closed and a window open, but outside smoking would be even better.

The apartment is only 3 flights up from the marble lobby/1st floor.  It is advised to bring luggage that isn't very heavy or to have luggage on rollers.  

A TV is not provided but light breakfast items can be, if requested (most people have not been using the ones I was providing, so English Muffins and mini bagels for toasting, buttery spread, jelly, cream cheese, a few pieces of fruit or juice can be provided upon request). 

Laundry facilities are available in the basement. 

The major benefits of this apartment are the nice decor, art works and furnishings; a large kitchen and living room; cleanliness and neatness of the place; very close proximity to many transportation lines, both subways and buses, and many taxis and car services; quick access to midtown and downtown; immediate access to Central Park (across the street); and very quick access to NYC's main museums (on "Museum Mile"), Columbia University, many different nearby restaurants that also deliver food, nearby nightspots, and numerous very good nearby supermarkets.

Who we are: Our Principles

1) Growing Our Alumni Community:
We don鈥檛 require any extra/hidden fees to maximize our profits. Instead, our focus is on growing our alumni community. Our one-month price is already competitive (averaging $1,200 to $2,200, with 80% of our 150 rooms under $1,900 per month), compared to others鈥?discounted prices for three- to six-month stays. In 2020, 50%+ of our customers extended their original stay by a few months. We provide co-living communities for our guests by helping property owners draw more value from under-managed residential properties. We care about our customer community, of course, but we鈥檙e also excited about uniting property owners, vendors, and our team on one digital platform.

鈥?) Privacy Is the Priority:
There are no required social events. Our priority is providing privacy, a quiet environment, and security for all our guests. Our team will take care of cleaning the common spaces every week, so that our kitchen/dining areas are always comfortable. But if you want to expand your network or social circle, our office at WeWork offers you day/after-work communities. 鈥?) 10 Years Perfecting the Co-Living Mindset:
Our founder started this business in his apartment after he couldn鈥檛 find appropriately priced accommodation for his first three months in New York. But our whole team has experienced co-living firsthand, so we understand what the customer feels and will need next. 鈥淲e live and breathe co-living: first as roommates, and now serving our co-living guests.鈥?鈥?
鈥?) A Sustainable Business Model in the Sharing Economy:
We won鈥檛 invest in luxury buildings like hotels or event spaces. We rent existing empty apartments and townhouses from the owners, put IKEA-type furniture in, and list the clean rooms on multiple digital platforms. We grow by our operational profit base, which comes from guests being charged fair prices and the revenue owners receive. However, what drives our growth is not the number of rooms, but our deep understanding of how to care for guests and rooms 24/7, and the intangible value within them.

CrossOver鈥檚 goal is to help our guests achieve their goals and dreams by providing the most affordable and flexible housing environment available. But it doesn鈥檛 stop here. Maraviglia is the land I grew up on, climbing the olive trees at age five and picking olives off the trees. After college and years living in big cities, I felt the need to go back to my roots and reconnect with the land that raised me.

Returning home, I witnessed first-hand the fragmented Tuscan Olive Oil industry, along with the slow extinction of an ancient craft. Something had to change, and so I decided to apply my business background to what I knew and make it better.

We don鈥檛 require any extra/hidden fees to maximize our profits. Instead, our focus is on growing our alumni community. 鈥?

Our one-month price is already competitive (averaging $1,200 to $2,200, with 80% of our 150 rooms under $1,900 per month), compared to others鈥?discounted prices for three- to six-month stays. When I was a little girl growing up in the South, I always used to fantasize that I was a child in New York City.  I would envision myself roller skating to school, going to see the Christmas tree in Rockefeller Center or swimming at the beach on Coney Island.  By the time I was four, I was determined to move to New York City when I grew up.  
Which I did.  And I raised my own four children here on a diverse block with the whole city as their school and playground.
They are all grown up now and their rooms lie empty.  The treehouse from which one could see Central Park is still in our backyard; their video games are still in the play loft we built for them; many of their surviving toys are in the room where my grandchildren play when they come to visit. 
But for days on end no children are here.
Meanwhile there are children all over the world who grow up with images of New York on their TV screens, in their books and in their movies.  They, too, want to experience the city for themselves.  And their parents want to bring them; but there are no other affordable accommodations specifically designed for families.  The only children who ever get to see New York are the offspring of the 1%.  
At this B&B, families can strengthen their bonds and create lifelong memories together as they visit all the iconic New York sites: The Statue of Liberty, Times Square, The Museum of Natural History.  But their children are also getting a taste of what it's like to be a New York City kid: playing stoop ball off our front steps, running through the sprinkler on our play street, eating ices off the corner hand truck.
In short, AIRBNB is New York City's ambassador to future generations.  Who knows?  They may grow up and bring their kids here to see this city, too, someday.

Our one-month price is already competitive (averaging $1,200 to $2,200, with 80% of our 150 rooms under $1,900 per month), compared to others鈥?discounted prices for three- to six-month stays. In 2020, 50%+ of our customers extended their original stay by a few months. There鈥檚 really no substitute for all-inclusive furnished rentals and a co-living environment, with a furnished private room, that鈥檚 ready for you on day one.

鈥?) Increasing Value for the Local Property Industry:
We provide co-living communities for our guests by helping property owners draw more value from under-managed residential properties. We care about our customer community, of course, but we鈥檙e also excited about uniting property owners, vendors, and our team on one digital platform.
鈥?
鈥?) Privacy Is the Priority:
There are no required social events. Our priority is providing privacy, a quiet environment, and security for all our guests. Our team will take care of cleaning the common spaces every week, so that our kitchen/dining areas are always comfortable. But if you want to expand your network or social circle, our office at WeWork offers you day/after-work communities. 鈥?) 10 Years Perfecting the Co-Living Mindset:
Our founder started this business in his apartment after he couldn鈥檛 find appropriately priced accommodation for his first three months in New York. 鈥?) A Sustainable Business Model in the Sharing Economy:
We won鈥檛 invest in luxury buildings like hotels or event spaces. We grow by our operational profit base, which comes from guests being charged fair prices and the revenue owners receive. 鈥?) A Sustainable Business Model in the Sharing Economy:
We won鈥檛 invest in luxury buildings like hotels or event spaces. We are world travelers that love meeting people and experiencing new cultures, customs & foods. As frequent travelers, and parents of two young boys (with another on the way), we never found hotels ideal for our needs as they often lacked the local character we were looking for and rarely provided space families need. We loved staying at Airbnbs but unfortunately had some unpleasant experience due to hosts that didn't take pride in their homes and the experience they provided.

As entrepreneurs, we decided to solve the problem ourselves which is why we started hosting ourselves and eventually created Rabbu. Rabbu is a full-service boutique-home experience company that provides guests with a local and authentic, yet consistently comfortable accommodation experience whether it be for one day or multiple months.

Keeping true to our backgrounds, Rabbu is inclusive of all guests no matter race or background. In fact, we encourage diversity and many of the properties that we operate are purposefully in true and authentic neighborhoods that feature lots of diversity and character. It truly is the best way to experience a city.

All of our units allow for self check-in and are professionally cleaned, provide free WiFi, toiletries and premium sheets/linens to ensure that guests have a comfortable experience. Guests will enjoy a worry-free stay while also being immersed in the authentic culture of the cities and neighborhoods they are visiting through our carefully selected and decorated spaces. We have also partnered with local service providers and restaurants to provide our guests with discounts, offers, services and recommendations which only locals are typically privileged to.

We live by a simple motto: 'Treat Others How You Wish To Be Treated' and that is the core value we have built Rabbu around. We want our guests to experience a city how we as travelers want to experience.

Come experience our properties and truly feel a part of the community you are visiting.

I'm Randy Settenbrino the artist who created the Historic Blue Moon and have been on Orchard Street from my teenage years as well as most of my professional life. The historic facades, merchants and eclectics give it the ambiance of a back lot 
from MGM. There is a soulfulness loved by the authentic locals as well as the out of Towner鈥檚 that gravitate here. The sensation of high energy is brought about by the contrast of old New York with the vigor of visitors to a burgeoning city. It's just the perfect scene to begin a story of your own or with someone of your choosing. There is room to mix in the crowd or make yourself noticed in a myriad of settings for human interaction; something surely missed in our time of impersonal communication. Any article about Orchard Street is incomplete without the newsworthy story of how the soul of a 5-story tenement filled with artifacts and personal affects became a stately eighth story hotel. Only a visit to the Historic Blue Moon can make one really understand how only on Orchard Street could art and history collide into such an elegant design.
The Historic Blue Moon was chosen as one in hundred and fifty hotels in the Western Hemisphere to check into by National Geographic as well as the recipient of over forty major articles.

Dear Airbnb guests!

Thanks for checking my profile. I manage furnished monthly rentals and co-living spaces in Manhattan, Queens, and Brooklyn with my team members. Who we are: Our Principles

1) Growing Our Alumni Community:
We don鈥檛 require any extra/hidden fees to maximize our profits. Instead, our focus is on growing our alumni community. We believe that our services and fair pricing speak for themselves among our guests. Our alumni posted 700+ reviews from 2019 to 2021. What鈥檚 more, 80% of the reviews gave us five stars and 97% awarded more than four stars. Our alumni community spans the globe with 87 unique nationalities, and it has been expanding. 鈥?
鈥?) Transparency. One All-Inclusive Price. That鈥檚 What We鈥檙e About:
There鈥檚 no math required. The price for our one-month minimum stay is simple and fair, no matter how long you stay with us. Our one-month price is already competitive (averaging $1,200 to $2,200, with 80% of our 150 rooms under $1,900 per month), compared to others鈥?discounted prices for three- to six-month stays. In 2020, 50%+ of our customers extended their original stay by a few months. There鈥檚 really no substitute for all-inclusive furnished rentals and a co-living environment, with a furnished private room, that鈥檚 ready for you on day one.
鈥?
鈥?) Increasing Value for the Local Property Industry:
We provide co-living communities for our guests by helping property owners draw more value from under-managed residential properties. We care about our customer community, of course, but we鈥檙e also excited about uniting property owners, vendors, and our team on one digital platform.
鈥?
鈥?) Privacy Is the Priority:
There are no required social events. Our priority is providing privacy, a quiet environment, and security for all our guests. Our team will take care of cleaning the common spaces every week, so that our kitchen/dining areas are always comfortable. But if you want to expand your network or social circle, our office at WeWork offers you day/after-work communities. We just moved our headquarters to the newest WeWork offices in Long Island City, which is easily accessible by all subway lines.


鈥?) 10 Years Perfecting the Co-Living Mindset:
Our founder started this business in his apartment after he couldn鈥檛 find appropriately priced accommodation for his first three months in New York. But our whole team has experienced co-living firsthand, so we understand what the customer feels and will need next. 鈥淲e live and breathe co-living: first as roommates, and now serving our co-living guests.鈥?鈥?
鈥?) A Sustainable Business Model in the Sharing Economy:
We won鈥檛 invest in luxury buildings like hotels or event spaces. We rent existing empty apartments and townhouses from the owners, put IKEA-type furniture in, and list the clean rooms on multiple digital platforms. We grow by our operational profit base, which comes from guests being charged fair prices and the revenue owners receive. However, what drives our growth is not the number of rooms, but our deep understanding of how to care for guests and rooms 24/7, and the intangible value within them.
鈥?
鈥?) Our Vision - Making Dreams Come True:
CrossOver鈥檚 goal is to help our guests achieve their goals and dreams by providing the most affordable and flexible housing environment available. But it doesn鈥檛 stop here. Our guests鈥?dreams are expanding to a variety of locations around the globe, and CrossOver will be right there with them鈥攑owering the dreams of residents, landlords, and our staff in the wider world.

We provide co-living communities for our guests by helping property owners draw more value from under-managed residential properties. We care about our customer community, of course, but we鈥檙e also excited about uniting property owners, vendors, and our team on one digital platform.
鈥?
鈥?) Privacy Is the Priority:
There are no required social events. Our priority is providing privacy, a quiet environment, and security for all our guests. Our founder started this business in his apartment after he couldn鈥檛 find appropriately priced accommodation for his first three months in New York. 鈥?) A Sustainable Business Model in the Sharing Economy:
We won鈥檛 invest in luxury buildings like hotels or event spaces. We rent existing empty apartments and townhouses from the owners, put IKEA-type furniture in, and list the clean rooms on multiple digital platforms. We grow by our operational profit base, which comes from guests being charged fair prices and the revenue owners receive. I'm Randy Settenbrino the artist who created the Historic Blue Moon and have been on Orchard Street from my teenage years as well as most of my professional life. The historic facades, merchants and eclectics give it the ambiance of a back lot 
from MGM. There is a soulfulness loved by the authentic locals as well as the out of Towner鈥檚 that gravitate here. The sensation of high energy is brought about by the contrast of old New York with the vigor of visitors to a burgeoning city. It's just the perfect scene to begin a story of your own or with someone of your choosing. There is room to mix in the crowd or make yourself noticed in a myriad of settings for human interaction; something surely missed in our time of impersonal communication. Any article about Orchard Street is incomplete without the newsworthy story of how the soul of a 5-story tenement filled with artifacts and personal affects became a stately eighth story hotel. Only a visit to the Historic Blue Moon can make one really understand how only on Orchard Street could art and history collide into such an elegant design.
The Historic Blue Moon was chosen as one in hundred and fifty hotels in the Western Hemisphere to check into by National Geographic as well as the recipient of over forty major articles.
